1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,260 --> 00:01:38,500
=Episode 1=

3
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:47,559
(Qingcheng District People's Court,
Tianhai City)

4
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:48,999
(The mythical beast, Xiezhi,)

5
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:51,990
(can tell right from wrong
and distinguish between good and evil.)

6
00:01:52,230 --> 00:01:54,279
(Tianhai City)
(It's a symbol of civil justice.)

7
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,589
(With that in mind,)

8
00:01:55,590 --> 00:01:56,999
(I became a judge.)

9
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,520
(Judge, Presiding Judge, Court Clerk)

10
00:01:58,830 --> 00:02:00,439
(However, a few months ago,)

11
00:02:00,440 --> 00:02:02,550
(I, who always longed
to work in a criminal court,)

12
00:02:02,750 --> 00:02:05,040
(was unexpectedly assigned
to the Family Court.)

13
00:02:05,240 --> 00:02:08,399
(Family Court)

14
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:10,340
(Mediation Room 1: In Use)
(What is a Family Court, you ask?)

15
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:14,560
(Family Court)
You guys are already married for eight years.

16
00:02:14,630 --> 00:02:16,640
You have the time to come to court,

17
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:18,719
but you don't have time to register
your child's household registration?

18
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:20,510
Of course that's your responsibility!

19
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:27,510
She was sent to
a juvenile detention center at 14.

20
00:02:32,510 --> 00:02:34,760
(Family Court presides over marriages,)

21
00:02:35,350 --> 00:02:36,670
(inheritances,)

22
00:02:37,070 --> 00:02:38,280
(division of family estate,)

23
00:02:38,750 --> 00:02:40,390
(alimony fees, and so on.)

24
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:42,719
(It's a court that specializes in)

25
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:44,760
(Court 1)
(family-related disputes.)

26
00:02:45,190 --> 00:02:47,790
(There are no cold
courtroom debates here.)

27
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:51,029
(There's no compelling
witness testimony.)

28
00:02:51,030 --> 00:02:53,480
(But there unfold the most hidden)

29
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:55,230
(yet genuine emotional entanglements)

30
00:02:55,590 --> 00:02:58,160
(every single day.)

31
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:01,080
(In Session)

32
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:06,630
The judges may take their seats.

33
00:03:11,920 --> 00:03:14,160
(Panel Judge)

34
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,390
Have a seat.

35
00:03:20,030 --> 00:03:22,480
Have a seat.

36
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:24,110
(Panel Judge)
Court is in session now.

37
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:27,670
(Family Court)
Court is in session now.

38
00:03:28,510 --> 00:03:29,719
Court is in session now.

39
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:31,840
(Panel Judge)

40
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:35,160
(Jindian Law Firm)

41
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:41,480
You're here today.

42
00:03:45,190 --> 00:03:46,950
I thought today was your rest day.

43
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:49,040
It's not like you'll receive
any bonuses for this.

44
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:50,480
You should head back.

45
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:53,440
What are you busy with?

46
00:03:57,440 --> 00:03:59,119
Mrs. Liu Lihua's case.

47
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:00,719
Everything's about to go down the drain.

48
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:02,760
Other cases might go through
rounds and rounds of back-and-forth

49
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:04,119
and still not end up with our firm.

50
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:04,719
Stop.

51
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:06,189
Don't ruin my mood.

52
00:04:06,190 --> 00:04:09,350
I still have to go to the friendly match
tomorrow in good spirits, you know?

53
00:04:11,030 --> 00:04:12,630
Friendly match?

54
00:04:13,070 --> 00:04:15,749
The more you network,
the fewer resources we have.

55
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:17,069
If you keep this up,

56
00:04:17,070 --> 00:04:18,520
next time, when our clients are here,

57
00:04:18,520 --> 00:04:21,120
we can't even afford to serve them tea
with disposable cups, you know?

58
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:23,440
Just skip it
if we don't have any tea leaves.

59
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:25,510
If so, use other cups, then.

60
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:28,760
Be careful. It's hot.

61
00:04:30,710 --> 00:04:31,949
Lin, you've truly changed.

62
00:04:31,950 --> 00:04:32,829
I've changed?

63
00:04:32,830 --> 00:04:35,280
When I first joined your law firm,
that wasn't what you told me.

64
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:36,120
What did I tell you?

65
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:36,919
You said,

66
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:38,629
I should work hard and give it my best.

67
00:04:38,630 --> 00:04:40,470
Living under the sky
and sea is no easy feat.

68
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:43,120
That children's rhyme sounded nice.

69
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:45,150
What are you saying?

70
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:50,359
It's already good enough as long as I
can earn enough to pay the utility fees.

71
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:52,880
I'll be eternally grateful to you
if you can make anything extra after that.

72
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:56,710
You're literally my meal card.

73
00:04:57,150 --> 00:04:58,880
I'm counting on you for my pension.

74
00:05:01,520 --> 00:05:04,720
(Qingcheng District People's Court,
Tianhai City)

75
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:08,599
Hello.

76
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,479
Morning.

77
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:10,359
Judge Shen.

78
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:12,560
This is the Family Division of
the Qingcheng District People's Court.

79
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:15,030
Your father, Zhao Shenfu,
filed a lawsuit against you.

80
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:16,920
Hello?

81
00:05:17,830 --> 00:05:19,030
Hello?

82
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:24,119
Let someone else call him.

83
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,800
He won't answer your calls today.

84
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:29,640
(Contact person: Zhao Ying)
This is the only person I haven't called.

85
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:50,880
Is this Wen Guoqiang?

86
00:05:51,070 --> 00:05:51,829
Yes.

87
00:05:51,830 --> 00:05:53,480
Please be advised
to appear at Courtroom No. 7

88
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:56,149
of the Qingcheng District
People's Court in Tianhai City at 9:00 A.M.

89
00:05:56,150 --> 00:05:57,919
on October 23, 2023
to attend the court hearing

90
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,269
in the case of Hu Tingting suing you
for unpaid child support.

91
00:05:59,270 --> 00:06:00,359
This telephone recording
has been notarized.

92
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:01,679
Hearing this
constitutes service of process.

93
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:03,509
Failure to appear in court
will result in legal consequences.

94
00:06:03,510 --> 00:06:05,309
If you are unable to attend due to
time constraints or other reasons,

95
00:06:05,310 --> 00:06:07,880
please call the court and contact me
to arrange an alternative time.

96
00:06:10,700 --> 00:06:11,749
How many times have I told you?

97
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:12,599
When making a call,

98
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,950
don't start by
identifying yourself right away.

99
00:06:15,190 --> 00:06:16,919
Confirm the receiver's
identity immediately.

100
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:18,749
After that, make sure to clearly
communicate the message

101
00:06:18,750 --> 00:06:20,710
you want to convey
to the other party right away.

102
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:25,069
I know that, but I don't have
a silver tongue like yours.

103
00:06:25,070 --> 00:06:26,309
Practice makes perfect.

104
00:06:26,310 --> 00:06:27,240
Okay.

105
00:06:28,150 --> 00:06:29,240
Are you Zhao Ying?

106
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:31,200
When it comes to custody of the child,

107
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:33,560
you might not necessarily
be able to win against the mother.

108
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,149
But you have to remember this.

109
00:06:35,150 --> 00:06:37,069
In court, make no accusations
or complaints.

110
00:06:37,070 --> 00:06:39,069
The assets go to her,
the debts go to you.

111
00:06:39,070 --> 00:06:40,950
Only talk about
fatherly love, not money.

112
00:06:42,150 --> 00:06:43,830
How will that do?

113
00:06:43,940 --> 00:06:46,149
If the judge passes that judgment,
doesn't that mean I'll incur a huge loss?

114
00:06:46,150 --> 00:06:47,829
Rest assured,
I will submit all of your claims

115
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:49,919
and evidence to the judge.

116
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:51,680
The judge will know what's going on
as soon as he sees it.

117
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:53,629
I'll definitely do my best
to secure those benefits for you.

118
00:06:53,630 --> 00:06:56,710
All you have to do is perfectly embody
the image of a perfect father

119
00:06:57,150 --> 00:06:58,629
and win the votes

120
00:06:58,630 --> 00:07:00,120
of the two female judges.

121
00:07:01,510 --> 00:07:02,950
Only the votes of the female judges?

122
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:04,309
What about the male judge?

123
00:07:04,310 --> 00:07:06,069
- I think his name is Shen...
- Shen Xiezhi.

124
00:07:06,070 --> 00:07:07,120
I've already looked him up.

125
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:08,709
There's a low possibility
of winning his vote.

126
00:07:08,710 --> 00:07:10,039
In the six months since he joined
Qingcheng District's court,

127
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:13,630
he has never awarded custody
of a child to the father.

128
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:17,709
The female judges will have
the mother's interests at heart.

129
00:07:17,710 --> 00:07:19,239
And now, you're telling me
to give up on the male judge.

130
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:21,840
Why don't I just forget about the lawsuit?
There's no way I can win anyway.

131
00:07:22,270 --> 00:07:23,629
Is this even a legitimate law firm?

132
00:07:23,630 --> 00:07:25,069
How are we not legitimate?

133
00:07:25,070 --> 00:07:28,309
How could you base the outcome
of my case on the judge's gender?

134
00:07:28,310 --> 00:07:29,269
You're so unprofessional.

135
00:07:29,270 --> 00:07:31,629
I'll go to another law firm, then.
I won't hire you.

136
00:07:31,630 --> 00:07:33,389
Alright, go then.

137
00:07:33,390 --> 00:07:35,039
You only gave me a 300-yuan deposit.

138
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:37,840
If you think you can find another law firm
with such cheap services, please go ahead.

139
00:07:37,840 --> 00:07:39,149
I won't take up your time.

140
00:07:39,150 --> 00:07:41,069
As it happens, Mr. Lin introduced
a VIP client to me,

141
00:07:41,070 --> 00:07:42,069
and he's coming in right after you.

142
00:07:42,070 --> 00:07:42,879
Let me clean the place up

143
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:44,709
- and prepare for him.
- Wait! Sit down.

144
00:07:44,710 --> 00:07:46,680
Sit down. Listen to me.

145
00:07:47,270 --> 00:07:48,039
I...

146
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:49,509
I was just a little impatient.

147
00:07:49,510 --> 00:07:50,799
You...

148
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:52,710
Don't take it to heart. Sit down.

149
00:07:57,800 --> 00:08:00,829
You have to
pay more attention to my case.

150
00:08:00,830 --> 00:08:02,760
Try your best to help me win, okay?

151
00:08:02,950 --> 00:08:04,749
Listen. I'll make sure
you'll get rewarded handsomely

152
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:06,880
as long as you win the lawsuit for me.

153
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:10,560
Alright.

154
00:08:10,950 --> 00:08:12,039
If you want to win,

155
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:13,159
you'd better listen to me.

156
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:13,999
(In Session)

157
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,949
Are you guys willing
to change your eating habits

158
00:08:15,950 --> 00:08:17,799
for each other's sake?

159
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:18,830
No way.

160
00:08:18,970 --> 00:08:20,599
Whenever I eat spicy food,
my body gets heaty.

161
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,149
She cannot live without spicy food.

162
00:08:22,150 --> 00:08:24,510
Well, wouldn't that be solved
if you two just had a mixed hot pot?

163
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,000
No way.

164
00:08:26,390 --> 00:08:27,709
Why not?

165
00:08:27,710 --> 00:08:30,309
She always stirs the soup
for no particular reason.

166
00:08:30,310 --> 00:08:32,029
And, the spicy soup
would get mixed with my clear soup.

167
00:08:32,030 --> 00:08:33,549
You don't stir the hot pot
when you're trying to grab food？

168
00:08:33,550 --> 00:08:35,079
I haven't even complained about you
watering down my spicy soup yet.

169
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:37,359
Clarify yourself.
What ingredient did I grab?

170
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:39,040
If so, just buy two separate pots,

171
00:08:39,150 --> 00:08:40,999
and have hot pot in separate rooms.

172
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:41,999
- No way.
- No way.

173
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,350
Why not?

174
00:08:44,030 --> 00:08:47,110
We don't usually cook at home.

175
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:50,749
The atmosphere of a hot pot restaurant
can never be replicated at home.

176
00:08:50,750 --> 00:08:52,119
You still dare to say that?

177
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,749
I know you enjoy the atmosphere there.

178
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:54,629
But what about me?

179
00:08:54,630 --> 00:08:55,789
Sir, look at this.

180
00:08:55,790 --> 00:08:57,429
My hands were scalded because of her.

181
00:08:57,430 --> 00:08:58,800
(Differences in habits)
Is this considered domestic abuse?

182
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:00,269
Shouldn't she get less of our assets?

183
00:09:00,270 --> 00:09:02,149
(Lack of communication）
You were the one who shook the table first.

184
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:04,269
You blame me for everything
whenever something goes wrong.

185
00:09:04,270 --> 00:09:05,239
Since when did I shake the table?

186
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:06,710
Everything is my fault!

187
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:10,269
(Blame each other
Endless arguing)

188
00:09:10,270 --> 00:09:12,110
(What is on the surface
is the essence itself.)

189
00:09:12,390 --> 00:09:14,119
(They've already lost control
of their emotions.)

190
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:15,119
(Highly agitated)

191
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:17,479
(Just a hot pot meal
can end up in court.)

192
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:19,669
(Tensions are high,
and neither side is backing down.)

193
00:09:19,670 --> 00:09:20,549
(Neither side is backing down)
(High tension)

194
00:09:20,550 --> 00:09:22,520
(It seems we can't
continue the session.)

195
00:09:23,270 --> 00:09:25,160
(Recess)
(Adjournment should be the best option.)

196
00:09:26,790 --> 00:09:28,320
Please observe court order.

197
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:34,509
Having different eating habits is different
from having different world views.

198
00:09:34,510 --> 00:09:36,280
Forcing you guys
to compromise with each other

199
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:39,920
will never be as optimal as you two
trying to know each other.

200
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:41,710
In the end,

201
00:09:42,150 --> 00:09:43,249
a court trial

202
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:45,560
cannot address the core issues
in a relationship.

203
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:49,029
Are both parties
willing to accept mediation?

204
00:09:49,030 --> 00:09:50,830
- No, I'm not.
- No, I'm not.

205
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:53,629
Given the intense animosity
between the two sides,

206
00:09:53,630 --> 00:09:55,560
it's difficult to make a major decision.

207
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,440
I hereby announce

208
00:09:57,510 --> 00:09:58,950
that the court is adjourned.

209
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:07,509
Youngsters nowadays

210
00:10:07,510 --> 00:10:09,119
shouldn't be trifled with.

211
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:11,830
She Xiezhi alone
is enough trouble for me.

212
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:14,549
What has that disciple of yours
gotten himself into again?

213
00:10:14,550 --> 00:10:15,719
What are you saying?

214
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:18,079
He's diligent and highly efficient.

215
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:20,680
He handed down
three judgments alone this morning.

216
00:10:21,270 --> 00:10:22,119
That's pretty good.

217
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:23,549
This quarter's case clearance rate

218
00:10:23,550 --> 00:10:25,479
is entirely thanks to him.

219
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:28,520
You and your disciple are indeed alike.

220
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,239
You two have the same

221
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:32,750
sharp tongue.

222
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,669
I dare not teach other people that.

223
00:10:34,670 --> 00:10:36,359
Chief Judge He was the one
who put him under me.

224
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:39,629
I think he thinks my thyroid nodule
isn't troublesome enough for me.

225
00:10:39,630 --> 00:10:41,029
That's why he did this to me.

226
00:10:41,030 --> 00:10:43,750
The deeper the love,
the harsher the criticism, huh?

227
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:46,549
Shen has an impressive case-closure rate

228
00:10:46,550 --> 00:10:48,149
and a low complaint rate.

229
00:10:48,150 --> 00:10:49,029
What does that prove?

230
00:10:49,030 --> 00:10:52,599
That means both parties
are fully convinced, right?

231
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:53,959
They can't wait to get out

232
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:56,870
of this legal trouble

233
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:58,640
and start a new life.

234
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:01,079
It sure feels good at the start.

235
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:02,389
He just passes down judgment

236
00:11:02,390 --> 00:11:03,839
without having a thorough
understanding of their issues.

237
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:06,640
What if the parties
regret their actions?

238
00:11:06,750 --> 00:11:09,629
You're always so indignant and furious.

239
00:11:09,630 --> 00:11:11,999
You also want to give the party involved
a chance to make amends, right?

240
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,710
Anyway, when I look at
a 30-year-old baby posing as a grown-up,

241
00:11:14,910 --> 00:11:16,710
I can't contain my anger.

242
00:11:17,430 --> 00:11:18,789
Even so, you have to contain it.

243
00:11:18,790 --> 00:11:20,560
This is our job after all.

244
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:22,440
Eat up.

245
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,149
Mom.

246
00:11:30,150 --> 00:11:31,909
I'll be full after finishing this corn.

247
00:11:31,910 --> 00:11:32,959
I won't finish the soup.

248
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:34,040
I'm already full.

249
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:35,839
How have things been going for you

250
00:11:35,840 --> 00:11:37,389
at the Family Court these past few days?

251
00:11:37,390 --> 00:11:38,239
It's okay, I guess.

252
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:40,319
It's just work.
My feelings don't matter that much.

253
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:41,959
Your father isn't home.

254
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:43,990
There's no need
to keep anything from me.

255
00:11:48,030 --> 00:11:51,719
I feel like the Family Court
shouldn't be considered a court.

256
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:53,120
It's more like a neighborhood committee.

257
00:11:53,150 --> 00:11:54,749
The judges there
don't seem like judges either.

258
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:56,040
What do they seem like, then?

259
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:03,990
Like the engineers of human souls.

260
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:05,549
For kindergartners.

261
00:12:05,550 --> 00:12:07,440
I have to coax and console
the parties involved every day.

262
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:16,640
Xiezhi, how come you're free enough
to come home today?

263
00:12:17,390 --> 00:12:19,389
I thought you were working overtime.
Why are you back?

264
00:12:19,390 --> 00:12:20,560
I finished my work early.

265
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:22,400
What's wrong?
Are you not busy with work?

266
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:26,509
Hurry. Wash your hands
and have dinner with us.

267
00:12:26,510 --> 00:12:27,719
I'll get you some rice.

268
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:30,680
Our son is rarely back. I want to have
a heartfelt conversation with him.

269
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:32,470
How is it,

270
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:33,800
Xiezhi?

271
00:12:36,840 --> 00:12:38,440
Is everything going smoothly

272
00:12:38,510 --> 00:12:40,119
in the Family Court?

273
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:41,350
Yeah.

274
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:42,680
It's just work.

275
00:12:42,910 --> 00:12:44,280
It's fine as long as I do my best.

276
00:12:44,910 --> 00:12:46,830
What do you mean by that?

277
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:48,149
You're a judge.

278
00:12:48,150 --> 00:12:49,629
You need to serve the people.

279
00:12:49,630 --> 00:12:51,800
Just like the dishes on our table,

280
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:54,040
if the cook isn't skilled enough,

281
00:12:54,430 --> 00:12:56,200
if he doesn't know how to handle a wok,

282
00:12:56,270 --> 00:12:57,789
if he cannot control the heat well,

283
00:12:57,790 --> 00:12:59,719
naturally, the consumer
won't be happy with the food.

284
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:00,879
Enough already.

285
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:02,199
Let's eat.

286
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:03,590
Let's eat.

287
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:05,959
Mom.

288
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:08,149
I don't think it's an issue
with the cook's skills.

289
00:13:08,150 --> 00:13:10,400
It's like you're making a five-star
chef cook at a roadside stall.

290
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:11,669
The five-star chef is more suited

291
00:13:11,670 --> 00:13:13,999
to prepare an extravagant feast.

292
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:16,470
But you just had to make him
work at a roadside stall.

293
00:13:16,960 --> 00:13:19,200
Isn't that a huge waste of talent?

294
00:13:19,910 --> 00:13:21,079
I'm full now.

295
00:13:21,080 --> 00:13:22,400
I'll head back first.

296
00:13:22,550 --> 00:13:23,750
You...

297
00:13:29,150 --> 00:13:31,640
It's rare for our son
to join us for a meal, you know?

298
00:13:31,790 --> 00:13:33,590
Can't you just shut up?

299
00:13:42,150 --> 00:13:44,110
(Outstanding Collective)
He's a talented boy indeed.

300
00:13:44,390 --> 00:13:47,070
But sometimes, he lacks empathy.

301
00:13:47,390 --> 00:13:49,870
He relies too heavily
on his own methodology.

302
00:13:50,270 --> 00:13:52,710
Xiezhi certainly has
a high opinion of himself.

303
00:13:52,750 --> 00:13:54,909
He thinks he's superior to others.

304
00:13:54,910 --> 00:13:57,400
That boy will never let his emotions
affect his work.

305
00:13:57,480 --> 00:13:58,830
However,

306
00:13:58,910 --> 00:13:59,629
I just don't know

307
00:13:59,630 --> 00:14:01,509
when he'll figure out

308
00:14:01,510 --> 00:14:02,389
why the organization

309
00:14:02,390 --> 00:14:03,959
sent him to us

310
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:05,560
for exchange purposes.

311
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:08,830
Morning, Mr. He.

312
00:14:09,430 --> 00:14:10,319
Xiezhi, you're here.

313
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:10,839
Alright.

314
00:14:10,840 --> 00:14:13,389
I'll notify you once I'm done
with the seminar's arrangement.

315
00:14:13,390 --> 00:14:14,400
See you.

316
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:21,590
What brings you here so early today?

317
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:24,830
Mr. He.

318
00:14:26,120 --> 00:14:27,719
I have no objections to the organization

319
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:28,870
assigning me here for training.

320
00:14:30,030 --> 00:14:31,320
It's just that...

321
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:32,800
Let me ask you something.

322
00:14:33,270 --> 00:14:35,280
Jiang Feng, who went to
the Intermediate People's Court

323
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:37,319
at the same time as you,

324
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:40,110
he recently received a transfer notice
from the High Court, right?

325
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:42,710
Yeah.

326
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:44,119
Look at you.

327
00:14:44,120 --> 00:14:45,789
Just now, I said on the phone

328
00:14:45,790 --> 00:14:48,029
that you wouldn't let your emotions
get the better of you.

329
00:14:48,030 --> 00:14:49,680
It seems like I was wrong.

330
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:51,719
Youngsters have ambitions,

331
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:53,029
and they wish to ascend the ranks
and develop their careers.

332
00:14:53,030 --> 00:14:54,750
That's very normal.

333
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:55,999
However,

334
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,599
you must never let your emotions

335
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:58,839
affect your work.

336
00:14:58,840 --> 00:14:59,990
Understood?

337
00:15:01,240 --> 00:15:02,199
Mr. He,

338
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:04,119
if you have any opinions
on my work attitude,

339
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:05,599
I can explain my actions one by one.

340
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:06,959
Every case underwent
the necessary mediation process

341
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:09,029
before a judgment was rendered.

342
00:15:09,030 --> 00:15:11,470
As for the three couples
I've presided over, they...

343
00:15:11,630 --> 00:15:13,999
I have no doubt about
your professional competence.

344
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:15,110
However,

345
00:15:15,510 --> 00:15:17,389
you need to remember
the most important point.

346
00:15:17,390 --> 00:15:18,669
You have to work seriously.

347
00:15:18,670 --> 00:15:19,999
Whenever you review a case,

348
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,480
you need to carefully consider

349
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:23,560
what the parties' fundamental
claims actually are.

350
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:25,070
Understood?

351
00:15:26,510 --> 00:15:28,280
You can go ahead. I'll be leaving now.

352
00:15:36,150 --> 00:15:37,749
Why did you have to take this to court?

353
00:15:37,750 --> 00:15:39,029
Just look at you.

354
00:15:39,030 --> 00:15:40,479
Is this the place you're supposed to be?

355
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:42,789
Can't we just discuss at home?

356
00:15:42,790 --> 00:15:43,789
Don't do this.

357
00:15:43,790 --> 00:15:45,319
You're so petty
that we ended up coming here.

358
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:46,479
Who knows what'll happen in the future?

359
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:47,029
Get ready.

360
00:15:47,030 --> 00:15:49,119
Three, two, one, go.

361
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:51,080
I just finished explaining
the security screening procedures

362
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:53,110
at this court to you all.

363
00:15:53,280 --> 00:15:55,319
It's truly troublesome.

364
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:56,749
And, this is a warm reminder.

365
00:15:56,750 --> 00:15:58,599
Getting married is fun at first,

366
00:15:58,600 --> 00:15:59,879
but divorce isn't.

367
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:01,149
You guys must think twice.

368
00:16:01,150 --> 00:16:02,429
Let me introduce the place again.

369
00:16:02,430 --> 00:16:04,269
The zone we're in right now

370
00:16:04,270 --> 00:16:06,119
is the Family Court's waiting zone.

371
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:07,239
Come with me.

372
00:16:07,240 --> 00:16:10,110
Over here. Follow me.

373
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:12,070
(Court 1)
So what's this?

374
00:16:12,270 --> 00:16:13,719
This is Court 1.

375
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:15,079
I, Ms. Lala,

376
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:17,549
have to go to Court 1
even for a simple lawsuit.

377
00:16:17,550 --> 00:16:19,599
I strive to be the first
no matter what I do.

378
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:21,070
Number 1.

379
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:21,909
Mister,

380
00:16:21,910 --> 00:16:23,269
please keep your phone away.

381
00:16:23,270 --> 00:16:24,719
This is the court.

382
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:25,669
I'll stop.

383
00:16:25,670 --> 00:16:26,959
Sorry about that.

384
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:28,879
Have the parties involved
for Court 1 arrived?

385
00:16:28,880 --> 00:16:29,800
Over here.

386
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:31,990
Bring your ID and the court notice.

387
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:32,509
Come.

388
00:16:32,510 --> 00:16:33,350
Okay.

389
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:36,029
Do you know something?

390
00:16:36,030 --> 00:16:38,200
Our defendant, who's an influencer,

391
00:16:38,370 --> 00:16:40,749
she's pretty popular on the Internet.

392
00:16:40,750 --> 00:16:42,879
I joined her live stream yesterday.

393
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:44,429
In less than half an hour,

394
00:16:44,430 --> 00:16:46,509
her fans had already
sent her virtual gifts

395
00:16:46,510 --> 00:16:48,160
worth over 8,000 yuan.

396
00:16:48,670 --> 00:16:49,749
According to the indictment,

397
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:51,520
her annual income exceeds one million.

398
00:16:52,270 --> 00:16:53,479
I think so.

399
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:55,830
Her husband is quite pitiful.

400
00:16:56,360 --> 00:16:57,950
He worked so hard

401
00:16:57,960 --> 00:16:59,239
to help her establish her profile.

402
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:01,320
Right when it's beginning to grow...

403
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:05,039
During the live stream,

404
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:07,469
I think she interacted more
with the photographer

405
00:17:07,470 --> 00:17:08,920
than her husband.

406
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:11,279
Say, do you think she's hiding something?
Is she not telling us the truth?

407
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:13,039
Do not make accusations
without evidence.

408
00:17:13,040 --> 00:17:13,989
Don't worry.

409
00:17:13,990 --> 00:17:15,519
This is just a speculation.

410
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:18,400
We do have basic professional ethics.

411
00:17:19,230 --> 00:17:20,880
I feel for their child.

412
00:17:21,630 --> 00:17:22,840
Yeah.

413
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:23,840
Hey.

414
00:17:25,190 --> 00:17:27,510
Who do you think we should
hand the child's custody to?

415
00:17:27,520 --> 00:17:29,950
If nothing goes wrong,
it should definitely go to the mother.

416
00:17:30,360 --> 00:17:31,759
Their daughter is still very young.

417
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:33,640
I don't think it's appropriate
to let her father raise her.

418
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:35,389
Besides, now that his wife
has run away from him,

419
00:17:35,390 --> 00:17:37,080
he no longer has any income sources.

420
00:17:37,150 --> 00:17:39,840
I'm sure Shen Xiezhi feels the same.

421
00:17:40,670 --> 00:17:42,149
This is quite rare.

422
00:17:42,150 --> 00:17:43,709
For once, the three of us

423
00:17:43,710 --> 00:17:45,519
don't have any disagreements.

424
00:17:45,520 --> 00:17:47,119
If so, I suppose
this will be a short session.

425
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:49,360
We're inside the courthouse.

426
00:17:49,520 --> 00:17:50,629
Look.

427
00:17:50,630 --> 00:17:51,709
It's so grand.

428
00:17:51,710 --> 00:17:53,510
The judges will sit there.

429
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:56,840
Ex-Husband.

430
00:17:57,760 --> 00:17:58,989
That's my ex-husband. Film him.

431
00:17:58,990 --> 00:18:00,149
Over here.

432
00:18:00,150 --> 00:18:01,310
Get out of the way.

433
00:18:02,040 --> 00:18:03,160
Go away.

434
00:18:08,320 --> 00:18:09,709
Hello, sir.

435
00:18:09,710 --> 00:18:11,400
Please keep your phone away.

436
00:18:11,470 --> 00:18:12,989
I'm one of you. I'm the defendant.

437
00:18:12,990 --> 00:18:14,389
No filming allowed in the courthouse.

438
00:18:14,390 --> 00:18:16,160
Those who are not involved,
please take a seat in the gallery.

439
00:18:16,230 --> 00:18:17,149
If so, you guys...

440
00:18:17,150 --> 00:18:17,759
Wait.

441
00:18:17,760 --> 00:18:18,920
Take this with you.

442
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:20,060
(The clerk)

443
00:18:20,430 --> 00:18:21,680
The clerk, huh?

444
00:18:24,430 --> 00:18:26,750
We will now proceed to verify
the individual's identity information.

445
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:29,750
Your ID.

446
00:18:31,430 --> 00:18:32,360
Thank you.

447
00:18:33,630 --> 00:18:34,919
I now call for court order.

448
00:18:35,510 --> 00:18:38,279
(Qingcheng District People's Court, Tianhai City)
Calling case number (2023) 2090

449
00:18:38,280 --> 00:18:39,880
Civil Case, First Instance No. 0319:

450
00:18:40,080 --> 00:18:41,229
Liu Wenbo

451
00:18:41,230 --> 00:18:42,119
versus Sun Lala,

452
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:43,680
regarding a matrimonial dispute.

453
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:45,559
On October 10, 2023,

454
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:47,079
this is the first public hearing.

455
00:18:47,080 --> 00:18:48,229
(Attorney, Plaintiff)

456
00:18:48,230 --> 00:18:50,989
Both parties claim that they are better
suited to raise the child.

457
00:18:50,990 --> 00:18:53,600
Please explain your reasons separately.

458
00:18:54,230 --> 00:18:57,319
We still believe it is more appropriate
for the child to live with our client.

459
00:18:57,320 --> 00:18:59,840
(Defendant)
Their child is almost five years old.

460
00:18:59,950 --> 00:19:01,279
She's about to go to school.

461
00:19:01,280 --> 00:19:03,389
If so, she needs
a local household registration

462
00:19:03,390 --> 00:19:05,030
and a home.

463
00:19:05,150 --> 00:19:07,149
What's the point of
a local household registration?

464
00:19:07,150 --> 00:19:08,079
Liu Wenbo,

465
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:10,469
do you want our child to enroll
in a school beside the farm?

466
00:19:10,470 --> 00:19:12,990
The plaintiff is speaking.
The defendant shouldn't interrupt.

467
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:14,990
- You'll get your turn later.
- Okay.

468
00:19:15,080 --> 00:19:17,629
I think which school she enrolls in
doesn't matter for now.

469
00:19:17,630 --> 00:19:21,279
We can secure school enrollment for
many schools by just renting a house nowadays.

470
00:19:21,280 --> 00:19:23,119
But at least someone needs
to cook for our child

471
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:25,039
and send her to
or pick her up from school

472
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:26,989
We were young when we first got married.

473
00:19:26,990 --> 00:19:28,680
We had no experience
in taking care of a child.

474
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:30,669
My mother raised the child up.

475
00:19:30,670 --> 00:19:32,270
Many times,

476
00:19:32,520 --> 00:19:34,949
the defendant visited nightclubs
without returning home for the night.

477
00:19:34,950 --> 00:19:36,189
Our child slept beside my mother.

478
00:19:36,190 --> 00:19:37,359
And, she slept well.

479
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:38,279
Liu Wenbo.

480
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:40,359
Don't try to put me on the spot here.

481
00:19:40,360 --> 00:19:41,389
I visited nightclubs, huh?

482
00:19:41,390 --> 00:19:42,759
What about you, then?

483
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:45,989
How many times have you slept
by the roadside after getting drunk?

484
00:19:45,990 --> 00:19:47,640
Defendant, do not interrupt.

485
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:48,359
Alright.

486
00:19:48,360 --> 00:19:49,840
Don't interrupt us.

487
00:19:51,040 --> 00:19:52,119
Presiding Judge,

488
00:19:52,120 --> 00:19:53,750
back then, I was young and insensible.

489
00:19:53,990 --> 00:19:55,669
Our child still had
both parents back then.

490
00:19:55,670 --> 00:19:57,429
But now, she only has her father left.

491
00:19:57,430 --> 00:19:59,039
If so, I have to be
a fatherly figure for her.

492
00:19:59,040 --> 00:20:01,189
Liu Wenbo,
aren't you embarrassed at all?

493
00:20:01,190 --> 00:20:03,120
Even I feel ashamed hearing that.

494
00:20:04,710 --> 00:20:06,880
Defendant, tell us about your family.

495
00:20:06,910 --> 00:20:09,229
Her parents got a divorce.
They remarried other people after that.

496
00:20:09,230 --> 00:20:10,160
I...

497
00:20:10,190 --> 00:20:11,949
And, they've gotten another divorce.

498
00:20:11,950 --> 00:20:13,359
They aren't even in Tianhai now.

499
00:20:13,360 --> 00:20:14,989
Presiding Judge, you can ask her.

500
00:20:14,990 --> 00:20:16,709
She might not even know whether
her parents are still alive or not.

501
00:20:16,710 --> 00:20:18,599
But I can hire a nanny.

502
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:20,559
It just costs 8,000 yuan per month.

503
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:22,470
I can easily hire a nanny.

504
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:27,310
(Here comes my chance.)

505
00:20:29,080 --> 00:20:32,400
Plaintiff, did you have
other income sources?

506
00:20:38,990 --> 00:20:42,149
I did plenty of jobs.
I have extensive social experience.

507
00:20:42,150 --> 00:20:43,519
That created a good foundation

508
00:20:43,520 --> 00:20:45,360
for my live streaming career.

509
00:20:46,190 --> 00:20:47,079
Him?

510
00:20:47,080 --> 00:20:48,799
He can only work
at a spot for at most three months.

511
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:50,470
After that, he sponges off
his parents for 20 years.

512
00:20:54,560 --> 00:20:55,839
If so, do you have any plans

513
00:20:55,840 --> 00:20:56,989
for your future career?

514
00:20:56,990 --> 00:20:58,640
I plan to start another
live stream account.

515
00:20:58,950 --> 00:20:59,839
You're creating a brand new account

516
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:02,079
with zero fans and traffic.

517
00:21:02,080 --> 00:21:03,759
Have you thought about
your projected income?

518
00:21:03,760 --> 00:21:05,559
It's not like she's the one
bringing in the money these days.

519
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:07,200
My daughter is the one.

520
00:21:07,710 --> 00:21:09,799
The fans are there just to watch...

521
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:12,359
The fans are there only because
they like to watch my daughter.

522
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:13,839
She? She has nothing to do with it.

523
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:15,039
Even so, I gave birth to our child

524
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:16,149
after being pregnant for ten months.

525
00:21:16,150 --> 00:21:16,909
And now, you want to take her away?

526
00:21:16,910 --> 00:21:17,669
What do you mean by that?

527
00:21:17,670 --> 00:21:18,989
You think I'll let you
use her as your cash cow?

528
00:21:18,990 --> 00:21:20,519
Anyone can become popular
if they own that account.

529
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:21,559
I've already given you the account.

530
00:21:21,560 --> 00:21:22,990
Why are you still not content?

531
00:21:23,150 --> 00:21:23,909
Fine.

532
00:21:23,910 --> 00:21:25,629
I'll give you the account.
Give me the child.

533
00:21:25,630 --> 00:21:26,880
Are you fine with that?

534
00:21:29,320 --> 00:21:30,079
Have you guys considered

535
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:32,149
the fact that your daughter
will go to school soon?

536
00:21:32,150 --> 00:21:34,359
Have you guys considered
letting her quit live streaming

537
00:21:34,360 --> 00:21:36,319
and opening a new account
for both of you respectively?

538
00:21:36,320 --> 00:21:37,680
- No.
- No way.

539
00:21:37,840 --> 00:21:39,559
If the parties cannot agree on

540
00:21:39,560 --> 00:21:40,629
custody of the child...

541
00:21:40,630 --> 00:21:41,680
- No.
- No.

542
00:21:41,840 --> 00:21:42,920
No.

543
00:21:46,630 --> 00:21:48,880
Let me emphasize this again.
Do not interrupt.

544
00:21:48,990 --> 00:21:51,200
Please do not disrupt
court proceedings from the gallery.

545
00:21:54,670 --> 00:21:56,750
Have you considered joint custody?

546
00:21:57,280 --> 00:21:58,359
Yes.

547
00:21:58,360 --> 00:22:01,799
No matter what, the defendant is still
our child's mother.

548
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:03,149
The only term I can accept

549
00:22:03,150 --> 00:22:04,989
is for me to keep the child

550
00:22:04,990 --> 00:22:06,189
on Monday, Wednesday, and Friday.

551
00:22:06,190 --> 00:22:08,229
She can keep her on
Tuesday, Thursday, and Saturday.

552
00:22:08,230 --> 00:22:09,389
For fairness's sake,

553
00:22:09,390 --> 00:22:11,079
the child can spend her Sunday
with my mother.

554
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:12,949
You sure know how to
play your cards right, huh?

555
00:22:12,950 --> 00:22:14,519
Can you promise me

556
00:22:14,520 --> 00:22:16,229
that you won't make our child
do a live stream on Sunday?

557
00:22:16,230 --> 00:22:17,389
If you can promise me that,

558
00:22:17,390 --> 00:22:18,879
I'll sign the agreement
with you immediately.

559
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:19,990
Sun Lala.

560
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:21,839
Streaming traffic is heaviest
on Saturdays and Sundays.

561
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:23,279
You already have the child on Saturday.

562
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:24,839
Why aren't you content yet?

563
00:22:24,840 --> 00:22:26,229
You want to make it fair, huh?

564
00:22:26,230 --> 00:22:27,559
Fine, then.

565
00:22:27,560 --> 00:22:29,629
For me, Tuesday, Thursday, and Saturday.
For you, Wednesday, Friday, and Sunday.

566
00:22:29,630 --> 00:22:31,160
Streaming traffic is lightest on Monday.

567
00:22:31,190 --> 00:22:32,039
Let's split it in half.

568
00:22:32,040 --> 00:22:32,989
What do you think? Tell me.

569
00:22:32,990 --> 00:22:33,950
You!

570
00:22:37,120 --> 00:22:38,799
The panel will ultimately
reach a decision on

571
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:40,119
who gets custody of the child

572
00:22:40,120 --> 00:22:42,080
and how visitation will be arranged.

573
00:22:42,190 --> 00:22:43,559
You guys have ten minutes.

574
00:22:43,560 --> 00:22:45,360
Think long and hard during this period.

575
00:22:46,280 --> 00:22:47,920
What did I tell you?

576
00:22:48,430 --> 00:22:50,440
Only talk about fatherly love, not money.

577
00:22:50,630 --> 00:22:51,909
We had a three-hour practice for this.

578
00:22:51,910 --> 00:22:53,310
And, it all went down the drain.

579
00:22:53,470 --> 00:22:54,839
That woman provoked me first.

580
00:22:54,840 --> 00:22:56,750
Is that even the point here?

581
00:22:57,040 --> 00:22:58,389
I told you already.

582
00:22:58,390 --> 00:23:01,429
Women have the advantage
when it comes to custody of the child.

583
00:23:01,430 --> 00:23:03,119
You have to perform
ten times better than her

584
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:04,710
just to stand a chance
to make a comeback.

585
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:06,229
But you?

586
00:23:06,230 --> 00:23:07,229
You went all in.

587
00:23:07,230 --> 00:23:08,559
Now, to the judges,

588
00:23:08,560 --> 00:23:10,990
you're inhumane and irresponsible.

589
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:11,949
As for who gets custody of the daughter,

590
00:23:11,950 --> 00:23:12,709
you'll just have to leave it up to fate.

591
00:23:12,710 --> 00:23:13,879
That won't do.

592
00:23:13,880 --> 00:23:15,119
You're the attorney I hired.

593
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:16,149
You can't just walk away.

594
00:23:16,150 --> 00:23:17,559
But you don't heed my advice at all.

595
00:23:17,560 --> 00:23:18,469
I'll heed your advice.

596
00:23:18,470 --> 00:23:19,790
Tell me. What should I do?

597
00:23:22,990 --> 00:23:24,559
Listen closely.

598
00:23:24,560 --> 00:23:25,759
Right now, you only won

599
00:23:25,760 --> 00:23:27,039
one of the three votes.

600
00:23:27,040 --> 00:23:27,709
Whose vote did I win?

601
00:23:27,710 --> 00:23:29,030
Judge Yu.

602
00:23:29,120 --> 00:23:30,669
She definitely came from
a well-off family.

603
00:23:30,670 --> 00:23:32,229
Her parents doted on her since young.

604
00:23:32,230 --> 00:23:34,790
She dislikes
your ex-wife's family of origin.

605
00:23:34,910 --> 00:23:36,709
When you're in the court,
you can maintain eye contact with her

606
00:23:36,710 --> 00:23:37,839
put on a smile,

607
00:23:37,840 --> 00:23:39,519
and just feign ignorance.

608
00:23:39,520 --> 00:23:40,920
Understood.

609
00:23:41,230 --> 00:23:43,149
But Ms. Qin, I have
something to ask you.

610
00:23:43,150 --> 00:23:45,080
I don't think I'll win the vote
of the Presiding Judge.

611
00:23:45,630 --> 00:23:47,510
She's very stern.

612
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:49,880
I panic whenever she stares at me.

613
00:23:50,120 --> 00:23:51,359
But,

614
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:54,990
I wish to try and
win the male judge's vote.

615
00:23:55,950 --> 00:23:58,680
I get the feeling that he likes me.

616
00:23:59,280 --> 00:24:00,470
He likes you?

617
00:24:01,360 --> 00:24:03,839
There were several times in court
when our eyes met,

618
00:24:03,840 --> 00:24:05,359
and I realized
that he was smiling at me.

619
00:24:05,360 --> 00:24:06,949
I think he might have

620
00:24:06,950 --> 00:24:10,279
a shred of sympathy for me.

621
00:24:10,280 --> 00:24:11,429
Mr. Liu,

622
00:24:11,430 --> 00:24:12,989
did you know there's a kind of smile

623
00:24:12,990 --> 00:24:16,030
that comes from laughing
at the absurdities of the world?

624
00:24:17,760 --> 00:24:19,469
Before my grandma slaughters a chicken,

625
00:24:19,470 --> 00:24:22,149
she'll touch the chicken's neck gently

626
00:24:22,150 --> 00:24:23,389
and say this,

627
00:24:23,390 --> 00:24:25,229
"Little chicken,
don't blame me for this."

628
00:24:25,230 --> 00:24:26,709
"I need to eat you to survive."

629
00:24:26,710 --> 00:24:27,519
What does that mean?

630
00:24:27,520 --> 00:24:29,550
He's smiling at you because
he intends to devour you!

631
00:24:29,840 --> 00:24:31,200
Remember what I said.

632
00:24:31,390 --> 00:24:33,230
Try to win the votes
of the two female judges.

633
00:24:33,520 --> 00:24:35,149
Stop exchanging glances with that guy.

634
00:24:35,150 --> 00:24:36,360
Understood.

635
00:24:36,630 --> 00:24:38,680
I didn't exchange glances with him.

636
00:24:40,230 --> 00:24:43,030
(Laughing at
the absurdities of the world, huh?)

637
00:24:43,040 --> 00:24:45,599
(So this is what you think of us.)

638
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:47,120
(You're pretty confident, aren't you?)

639
00:24:47,470 --> 00:24:49,160
Have you guys made up your mind?

640
00:24:49,320 --> 00:24:51,759
With the child's well-being in mind,

641
00:24:51,760 --> 00:24:52,599
if either party

642
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:54,389
has any grounds or evidence,

643
00:24:54,390 --> 00:24:55,629
you may present them now.

644
00:24:55,630 --> 00:24:56,990
Ma'am.

645
00:24:57,190 --> 00:24:58,319
I have nothing to present,

646
00:24:58,320 --> 00:24:59,759
but I have something to say.

647
00:24:59,760 --> 00:25:00,599
I gave birth to our daughter

648
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:01,519
after being pregnant

649
00:25:01,520 --> 00:25:03,469
for ten whole months.

650
00:25:03,470 --> 00:25:04,839
How could I not dote on her?

651
00:25:04,840 --> 00:25:06,119
As the saying goes,

652
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:07,429
when a child gets a stepmother,

653
00:25:07,430 --> 00:25:09,229
even her real father
will become her stepfather.

654
00:25:09,230 --> 00:25:11,599
Once he remarries and has another child,

655
00:25:11,600 --> 00:25:13,080
My daughter will be...

656
00:25:13,120 --> 00:25:14,510
Presiding Judge.

657
00:25:14,910 --> 00:25:15,599
Yes, Plaintiff?

658
00:25:15,600 --> 00:25:17,359
I believe
that based on fairness and the law,

659
00:25:17,360 --> 00:25:19,359
custody of the child
should be granted to me.

660
00:25:19,360 --> 00:25:21,989
Over the past few years,
I've been working day and night,

661
00:25:21,990 --> 00:25:23,629
- just to do live streams every morning.
- I...

662
00:25:23,630 --> 00:25:25,030
Plaintiff, please be seated.

663
00:25:28,280 --> 00:25:29,680
Sit down and talk.

664
00:25:31,280 --> 00:25:33,559
During the day,
I'm busy with live streams.

665
00:25:33,560 --> 00:25:35,519
At night, I'm either
planning video content

666
00:25:35,520 --> 00:25:37,189
or burning
the midnight oil editing videos.

667
00:25:37,190 --> 00:25:39,189
I worked day and night
for the sake of this family.

668
00:25:39,190 --> 00:25:42,080
I've been pushing my body
to its limits for a long time now.

669
00:25:42,230 --> 00:25:43,909
Let's leave aside for now whether
I'll ever have the chance to remarry.

670
00:25:43,910 --> 00:25:44,709
Even if I do remarry,

671
00:25:44,710 --> 00:25:46,400
there's no way I can have another child.

672
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:52,160
What do you mean by that?

673
00:25:53,320 --> 00:25:55,200
Are you infertile now?

674
00:26:06,230 --> 00:26:07,989
Did your attorney tell you to say that?

675
00:26:07,990 --> 00:26:08,839
You guys are truly terrible.

676
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:10,469
How could you come up
with such a despicable trick?

677
00:26:10,470 --> 00:26:11,359
Presiding Judge!

678
00:26:11,360 --> 00:26:13,400
Defendant, mind your conduct.

679
00:26:14,990 --> 00:26:15,989
Plaintiff's attorney.

680
00:26:15,990 --> 00:26:18,709
I do not accept
the defendant's baseless accusations

681
00:26:18,710 --> 00:26:19,599
and insults against me.

682
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:20,949
Without any evidence,

683
00:26:20,950 --> 00:26:23,710
you cannot accuse my client of lying.

684
00:26:24,080 --> 00:26:25,879
And, you guys were already separated.

685
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:27,799
You have no say in this matter.

686
00:26:27,800 --> 00:26:28,879
I have no say in this matter?

687
00:26:28,880 --> 00:26:30,469
Do you think you have
a say in this matter, then?

688
00:26:30,470 --> 00:26:31,429
What?

689
00:26:31,430 --> 00:26:32,759
Have you slept with him or what?

690
00:26:32,760 --> 00:26:33,359
Presiding Judge!

691
00:26:33,360 --> 00:26:34,750
You shameless wretch!

692
00:26:35,910 --> 00:26:36,839
Defendant,

693
00:26:36,840 --> 00:26:37,949
do not make personal attacks

694
00:26:37,950 --> 00:26:39,319
against the plaintiff's attorney.

695
00:26:39,320 --> 00:26:40,400
Plaintiff.

696
00:26:40,600 --> 00:26:42,909
Is there any medical evidence

697
00:26:42,910 --> 00:26:44,710
to support the claim
that you are infertile?

698
00:26:46,760 --> 00:26:48,229
Why would I keep it with me?

699
00:26:48,230 --> 00:26:49,920
The diagnosis is already
embarrassing enough.

700
00:26:58,230 --> 00:27:00,080
Is what you said in court true or false?

701
00:27:01,630 --> 00:27:03,230
I made it up.

702
00:27:03,760 --> 00:27:04,389
You!

703
00:27:04,390 --> 00:27:05,640
What?

704
00:27:06,150 --> 00:27:07,230
You...

705
00:27:07,430 --> 00:27:09,599
Weren't you just talking nonsense, then?

706
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:12,270
You could face
legal consequences for this, you know?

707
00:27:13,080 --> 00:27:15,319
You told me to act pitiful, right?

708
00:27:15,320 --> 00:27:17,039
Isn't that pitiful enough?

709
00:27:17,040 --> 00:27:19,279
I told you to act pitiful,
but I didn't tell you to forge evidence.

710
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:21,319
Who can say for sure, right?

711
00:27:21,320 --> 00:27:23,839
Say, it's been so many years
since I last went for a medical checkup.

712
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:24,949
I worked so hard every day.

713
00:27:24,950 --> 00:27:26,759
It's perfectly normal for me
to have a few health issues.

714
00:27:26,760 --> 00:27:27,629
And, that's not the main thing.

715
00:27:27,630 --> 00:27:29,319
Since I already hired you,

716
00:27:29,320 --> 00:27:31,469
you have to help me handle this.

717
00:27:31,470 --> 00:27:32,429
If there's an additional charge,

718
00:27:32,430 --> 00:27:33,629
just let me know the amount in advance.

719
00:27:33,630 --> 00:27:35,440
You want me to take care of it for you?

720
00:27:35,840 --> 00:27:38,039
You need to go to a top-tier hospital
for this kind of examination.

721
00:27:38,040 --> 00:27:39,079
You should go.

722
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:41,400
Go and get me a report or something.

723
00:27:42,150 --> 00:27:43,440
Listen.

724
00:27:43,840 --> 00:27:45,469
If I do it, I'll face
legal consequences.

725
00:27:45,470 --> 00:27:46,840
I can't help you out.

726
00:27:49,990 --> 00:27:50,799
Why are you useless

727
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:52,510
during such crucial moments?

728
00:28:07,840 --> 00:28:09,510
Do you guys think

729
00:28:09,560 --> 00:28:10,709
he's speaking the truth?

730
00:28:10,710 --> 00:28:11,790
What?

731
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:13,440
Liu Wenbo.

732
00:28:13,910 --> 00:28:15,920
He said he was infertile.

733
00:28:17,630 --> 00:28:18,880
It's fake.

734
00:28:19,280 --> 00:28:20,189
How would you know?

735
00:28:20,190 --> 00:28:21,470
If it were true,

736
00:28:21,600 --> 00:28:23,230
they would've handed over
the evidence to us from the start.

737
00:28:23,390 --> 00:28:24,949
It's obvious that they made up
the story on the spot.

738
00:28:24,950 --> 00:28:26,440
And, that attorney is...

739
00:28:27,190 --> 00:28:27,989
Do you know her?

740
00:28:27,990 --> 00:28:29,200
I don't.

741
00:28:29,560 --> 00:28:31,389
But she couldn't cover her expression.

742
00:28:31,390 --> 00:28:33,200
Who do you think
should have custody of the child?

743
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:34,709
The father.

744
00:28:34,710 --> 00:28:35,629
Why?

745
00:28:35,630 --> 00:28:36,669
Although both parents

746
00:28:36,670 --> 00:28:38,510
treat their daughter as a cash cow,

747
00:28:38,520 --> 00:28:40,079
the mother's parents

748
00:28:40,080 --> 00:28:42,160
had a complicated marital situation.

749
00:28:43,360 --> 00:28:44,279
Her family of origin

750
00:28:44,280 --> 00:28:46,669
should have a negative influence on her.

751
00:28:46,670 --> 00:28:48,160
Look at the mother.

752
00:28:48,210 --> 00:28:50,229
She lived together with
the photographer right after separation.

753
00:28:50,230 --> 00:28:51,879
How is she a responsible mother?

754
00:28:51,880 --> 00:28:53,119
In comparison,

755
00:28:53,120 --> 00:28:55,879
the father's family of origin
is much more normal.

756
00:28:55,880 --> 00:28:59,200
After all, he has a hardworking,
down-to-earth, and selfless mother.

757
00:28:59,230 --> 00:29:02,599
That's great for
the child's development in the future.

758
00:29:02,600 --> 00:29:03,519
Right now, you only won

759
00:29:03,520 --> 00:29:05,790
one of the three votes,
which is Judge Yu's.

760
00:29:06,120 --> 00:29:08,519
She dislikes
your ex-wife's family of origin.

761
00:29:08,520 --> 00:29:10,359
When you're in the court,
you can maintain eye contact with her

762
00:29:10,360 --> 00:29:11,600
put on a smile,

763
00:29:11,760 --> 00:29:13,950
and just feign ignorance.
It'll definitely work out.

764
00:29:17,040 --> 00:29:18,880
Xiezhi, what do you think?

765
00:29:21,840 --> 00:29:23,080
I...

766
00:29:24,230 --> 00:29:26,230
How could you still hesitate?

767
00:29:27,840 --> 00:29:29,950
The girl is not even five years old.

768
00:29:30,560 --> 00:29:32,079
Her father sponges off his wife
while her mother earns a lot.

769
00:29:32,080 --> 00:29:33,149
With these details in mind,

770
00:29:33,150 --> 00:29:35,359
once you insert these details
in that judgment program of yours,

771
00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:36,709
the result will come out immediately.

772
00:29:36,710 --> 00:29:37,920
"Her mother" is the answer.

773
00:29:38,430 --> 00:29:40,160
How could you still hesitate?

774
00:29:40,470 --> 00:29:42,279
The case is still pending.

775
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:44,469
The parties are still
submitting new evidence.

776
00:29:44,470 --> 00:29:47,160
We should be more open-minded.

777
00:29:49,280 --> 00:29:50,950
Trying to act all high
and mighty, aren't you?

778
00:29:51,320 --> 00:29:53,429
This isn't a collegial deliberation.

779
00:29:53,430 --> 00:29:55,039
Why are you so serious?

780
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:57,149
Still submitting new evidence?

781
00:29:57,150 --> 00:29:58,709
Could it be that you think

782
00:29:58,710 --> 00:30:00,840
Liu Wenbo is actually infertile?

783
00:30:01,630 --> 00:30:03,799
Better safe than sorry.

784
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:04,990
Who can say for sure?

785
00:30:15,230 --> 00:30:16,319
Mr. Zhou.

786
00:30:16,320 --> 00:30:16,989
Sorry about that.

787
00:30:16,990 --> 00:30:18,669
My court hearing ended
a little later than expected.

788
00:30:18,670 --> 00:30:19,990
Sorry for the wait.

789
00:30:20,560 --> 00:30:21,989
Why don't I wait for you
at your law firm?

790
00:30:21,990 --> 00:30:24,030
It's right opposite the court
of Qingcheng District, right?

791
00:30:24,080 --> 00:30:26,600
I'll be there in a second.
Please stay there.

792
00:30:45,630 --> 00:30:46,920
Mr. Zhou.

793
00:30:48,910 --> 00:30:49,989
We finally meet.

794
00:30:49,990 --> 00:30:50,920
Hello.

795
00:30:53,190 --> 00:30:54,359
I'm truly sorry about this.

796
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:56,189
I should've been here
an hour and a half ago.

797
00:30:56,190 --> 00:30:58,599
- I thought that it would end by 15:30.
- Okay.

798
00:30:58,600 --> 00:30:59,559
I was late for over an hour.

799
00:30:59,560 --> 00:31:00,469
Yeah.

800
00:31:00,470 --> 00:31:01,790
Here's a small gift for you.

801
00:31:02,320 --> 00:31:03,310
It's okay.

802
00:31:05,670 --> 00:31:06,669
This is inappropriate.

803
00:31:06,670 --> 00:31:07,709
We cannot accept gifts from clients.

804
00:31:07,710 --> 00:31:09,790
It's nothing valuable.

805
00:31:09,800 --> 00:31:10,909
We cannot do this.

806
00:31:10,910 --> 00:31:12,599
You see, it's just a water tumbler.

807
00:31:12,600 --> 00:31:13,189
And a notebook

808
00:31:13,190 --> 00:31:14,710
that you've been using.

809
00:31:15,120 --> 00:31:16,279
It's the same one.

810
00:31:16,280 --> 00:31:17,880
You're too courteous.

811
00:31:18,040 --> 00:31:19,319
What beverage do you want?

812
00:31:19,320 --> 00:31:20,319
It's fine.

813
00:31:20,320 --> 00:31:21,469
My throat wasn't feeling well.

814
00:31:21,470 --> 00:31:23,120
I brought some Pangdahai tea with me.

815
00:31:23,630 --> 00:31:25,120
What case were you
dealing with just now?

816
00:31:26,430 --> 00:31:27,189
It's the same as yours.

817
00:31:27,190 --> 00:31:28,840
It's related to custody of the child.

818
00:31:28,950 --> 00:31:31,039
So it dragged on for over an hour, huh?

819
00:31:31,040 --> 00:31:32,470
Can you win the case?

820
00:31:32,760 --> 00:31:34,880
We'll definitely win.

821
00:31:36,470 --> 00:31:37,629
Definitely?

822
00:31:37,630 --> 00:31:39,189
You're very confident, huh?

823
00:31:39,190 --> 00:31:40,469
Why is that?

824
00:31:40,470 --> 00:31:42,360
Did you pull some strings

825
00:31:43,360 --> 00:31:45,360
with the judges?

826
00:31:48,390 --> 00:31:50,599
Pull some strings? What strings?

827
00:31:50,600 --> 00:31:51,799
We have the advantage here.

828
00:31:51,800 --> 00:31:52,949
We just need to present our evidence

829
00:31:52,950 --> 00:31:54,359
to the judges in full.

830
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:56,519
Although both cases
have the same goal in mind,

831
00:31:56,520 --> 00:31:58,840
my case is different from any other cases.

832
00:31:59,140 --> 00:32:00,360
That ex-wife of mine,

833
00:32:01,190 --> 00:32:02,750
she used internal connections.

834
00:32:02,950 --> 00:32:04,879
She said she found
someone pretty impressive.

835
00:32:04,880 --> 00:32:06,669
Let's not worry about
whether we can pull some strings too.

836
00:32:06,670 --> 00:32:09,270
Even if we do, I still need to find
someone impressive as well.

837
00:32:09,470 --> 00:32:12,710
You see, I invited you here today because

838
00:32:12,880 --> 00:32:13,990
I...

839
00:32:14,840 --> 00:32:16,550
I just want

840
00:32:16,880 --> 00:32:17,799
to ask you something.

841
00:32:17,800 --> 00:32:19,149
Your law firm

842
00:32:19,150 --> 00:32:20,750
and the director of your firm,

843
00:32:20,800 --> 00:32:22,640
which higher-up
are you guys familiar with?

844
00:32:28,230 --> 00:32:29,400
You see,

845
00:32:30,910 --> 00:32:32,440
logically speaking,

846
00:32:32,950 --> 00:32:34,080
we know all of them.

847
00:32:34,360 --> 00:32:36,160
What do you mean by that?

848
00:32:36,560 --> 00:32:39,160
Knowing them and being their friends
are two different matters, you know?

849
00:32:40,670 --> 00:32:42,279
For example, normal acquaintance is 1,

850
00:32:42,280 --> 00:32:43,279
and super close is 10.

851
00:32:43,280 --> 00:32:44,469
From 1 to 10,

852
00:32:44,470 --> 00:32:46,759
how close are you

853
00:32:46,760 --> 00:32:47,989
to which leader?

854
00:32:47,990 --> 00:32:49,790
Just tell me, okay?

855
00:32:51,670 --> 00:32:55,400
At least it's a 1.0.

856
00:32:58,760 --> 00:32:59,990
Maybe 2.0?

857
00:33:02,600 --> 00:33:04,470
Since it's been so long,

858
00:33:04,560 --> 00:33:05,909
the score might be

859
00:33:05,910 --> 00:33:07,360
3, 4, 5, even 6.

860
00:33:09,150 --> 00:33:10,510
I...

861
00:33:10,670 --> 00:33:11,389
You...

862
00:33:11,390 --> 00:33:12,709
You think I'm joking with you?

863
00:33:12,710 --> 00:33:15,790
Just tell me which judge

864
00:33:16,150 --> 00:33:18,519
are you guys close to.

865
00:33:18,520 --> 00:33:20,879
The kind that you can
request him to do things.

866
00:33:20,880 --> 00:33:22,839
And he will receive this, understood?

867
00:33:22,840 --> 00:33:24,279
Just tell me already.

868
00:33:24,280 --> 00:33:25,360
You see,

869
00:33:25,990 --> 00:33:27,949
even if our director does
involve himself in such affairs,

870
00:33:27,950 --> 00:33:29,519
he can't just tell me about it.

871
00:33:29,520 --> 00:33:30,879
If so, why the heck did I wait

872
00:33:30,880 --> 00:33:32,080
over an hour for you?

873
00:33:34,430 --> 00:33:35,229
What about this?

874
00:33:35,230 --> 00:33:37,200
Tell your director to come.

875
00:33:38,280 --> 00:33:39,880
You see,

876
00:33:39,950 --> 00:33:41,510
he usually deals with

877
00:33:41,800 --> 00:33:43,319
bankruptcies of listed companies,

878
00:33:43,320 --> 00:33:44,759
investment and financing, and so on.

879
00:33:44,760 --> 00:33:46,989
Those are all projects
worth tens of millions or more.

880
00:33:46,990 --> 00:33:48,470
He doesn't handle household matters.

881
00:33:59,800 --> 00:34:01,080
Mr. Zhou?

882
00:34:01,630 --> 00:34:02,680
You...

883
00:34:06,760 --> 00:34:07,950
Mr. Zhou?

884
00:34:09,070 --> 00:34:10,160
Mr. Zhou!

885
00:34:12,070 --> 00:34:13,359
Mr. Zhou,

886
00:34:13,360 --> 00:34:14,069
don't leave yet!

887
00:34:14,070 --> 00:34:15,359
If you wish to find our director,

888
00:34:15,360 --> 00:34:16,680
I can arrange an appointment for you.

889
00:34:16,720 --> 00:34:18,000
It's just

890
00:34:18,160 --> 00:34:19,430
that he's quite busy.

891
00:34:20,550 --> 00:34:21,870
He's quite busy?

892
00:34:22,160 --> 00:34:23,359
You think I'm joking
with you, aren't you?

893
00:34:23,360 --> 00:34:24,429
You think I'm fooling around?

894
00:34:24,430 --> 00:34:26,000
Why do you think I'm going to court?

895
00:34:26,240 --> 00:34:27,429
To see your child.

896
00:34:27,430 --> 00:34:28,790
In order to do that,

897
00:34:29,800 --> 00:34:32,160
I have to fight my ex-wife
for his custody.

898
00:34:37,030 --> 00:34:39,310
It's been half a year
since I last saw my son.

899
00:34:44,200 --> 00:34:45,480
You see, I...

900
00:34:46,760 --> 00:34:48,910
I think you have it rough too.

901
00:34:50,070 --> 00:34:52,359
Why did you think
I approached your law firm?

902
00:34:52,360 --> 00:34:53,909
I should go to the CBD

903
00:34:53,910 --> 00:34:56,469
and look for a law firm
in one of those skyscrapers!

904
00:34:56,470 --> 00:34:58,839
Or a law firm in one
of those detached villas!

905
00:34:58,840 --> 00:34:59,679
Why did you think I hire

906
00:34:59,680 --> 00:35:01,589
a small-time attorney
from a run-down little law firm

907
00:35:01,590 --> 00:35:04,230
right outside the courthouse
to handle my case?

908
00:35:08,030 --> 00:35:09,949
I approached you guys because I knew

909
00:35:09,950 --> 00:35:11,909
that your firm might not be able
to find major cases to take on.

910
00:35:11,910 --> 00:35:13,679
You scrape by on the crumbs

911
00:35:13,680 --> 00:35:15,960
that fall through the cracks
at all those big law firms.

912
00:35:15,990 --> 00:35:17,600
That's how you manage to survive.

913
00:35:18,110 --> 00:35:19,719
At the very least, you guys are
at the entrance to the People's Court.

914
00:35:19,720 --> 00:35:22,159
So you must've gotten
to know the judges a bit, right?

915
00:35:22,160 --> 00:35:23,469
If you guys know them,

916
00:35:23,470 --> 00:35:25,310
you'll be able to help me out.

917
00:35:25,950 --> 00:35:27,069
But when I ask you
whether you know them or not,

918
00:35:27,070 --> 00:35:28,109
you said

919
00:35:28,110 --> 00:35:31,350
your friendship level with them is a 1, 2,

920
00:35:31,640 --> 00:35:32,910
3, 4, 5, and 6? On a scale from 1 to 10?

921
00:35:35,470 --> 00:35:37,310
Who can help me out, then?

922
00:35:37,510 --> 00:35:38,549
You guys are pretty bizarre.

923
00:35:38,550 --> 00:35:39,549
How is your law firm

924
00:35:39,550 --> 00:35:41,350
able to make a living
in the first place?

925
00:35:41,840 --> 00:35:43,430
Don't you guys need money to survive?

926
00:35:45,030 --> 00:35:46,910
My goodness.
Why did I approach you guys?

927
00:35:47,160 --> 00:35:48,640
I must be blind.

928
00:36:03,550 --> 00:36:04,679
Ms. Qin.

929
00:36:04,680 --> 00:36:05,639
Ms. Qin.

930
00:36:05,640 --> 00:36:06,989
When the hearing starts,

931
00:36:06,990 --> 00:36:08,960
you'll still have to stand up for me.

932
00:36:09,160 --> 00:36:10,199
You don't know my husband.

933
00:36:10,200 --> 00:36:12,069
He knows all about my weaknesses.

934
00:36:12,070 --> 00:36:14,389
I wanted to perform well,

935
00:36:14,390 --> 00:36:16,390
but whenever I see him, I...

936
00:36:17,070 --> 00:36:18,389
Remember, when you're in court,

937
00:36:18,390 --> 00:36:19,989
don't keep eye contact
with your husband.

938
00:36:19,990 --> 00:36:21,029
Don't talk to him either.

939
00:36:21,030 --> 00:36:22,430
Don't look him in the eyes.

940
00:36:22,550 --> 00:36:25,469
As for me, I'll go over all
of your husband's charges

941
00:36:25,470 --> 00:36:26,719
with the judges first.

942
00:36:26,720 --> 00:36:28,069
Once I'm done,

943
00:36:28,070 --> 00:36:29,679
tell the judge everything

944
00:36:29,680 --> 00:36:31,359
about the hardships
you've endured over the years

945
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:32,989
while raising your three children.

946
00:36:32,990 --> 00:36:35,159
Remember, you have to shed tears
and pretend to be pitiful.

947
00:36:35,160 --> 00:36:36,469
You have to make the judges
feel sorry for you.

948
00:36:36,470 --> 00:36:36,989
If so, the judges

949
00:36:36,990 --> 00:36:38,429
will definitely side with us.

950
00:36:38,430 --> 00:36:40,000
By then, he'll definitely
ask your husband

951
00:36:40,160 --> 00:36:42,549
whether or not he felt guilty toward you

952
00:36:42,550 --> 00:36:44,640
and what would he do
to make it up to you.

953
00:36:44,800 --> 00:36:45,239
Am I right?

954
00:36:45,240 --> 00:36:47,350
After that, the judge will ask you this.

955
00:36:47,760 --> 00:36:48,589
He'll say,

956
00:36:48,590 --> 00:36:50,509
"Have you decided
to forgive your husband?"

957
00:36:50,510 --> 00:36:52,389
"Are you willing
to give him another chance?"

958
00:36:52,390 --> 00:36:53,109
At this moment,

959
00:36:53,110 --> 00:36:55,080
you get to state your conditions.

960
00:36:55,110 --> 00:36:57,159
At that moment, you can make
your husband return home.

961
00:36:57,160 --> 00:36:58,159
Make sure he returns home regularly.

962
00:36:58,160 --> 00:36:59,639
I'll add a deadline then,

963
00:36:59,640 --> 00:37:01,719
and include all the conditions
in the terms and conditions.

964
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:03,199
As long as a judge is overseeing him,

965
00:37:03,200 --> 00:37:04,469
the pressure
will definitely be different.

966
00:37:04,470 --> 00:37:06,279
If he fails to comply with the deadline,
you can file for divorce again.

967
00:37:06,280 --> 00:37:07,159
Do not tolerate his demeanor.

968
00:37:07,160 --> 00:37:08,230
And that's all.

969
00:37:10,200 --> 00:37:11,469
I'll file for divorce
if he doesn't return home.

970
00:37:11,470 --> 00:37:12,549
Don't worry.

971
00:37:12,550 --> 00:37:14,680
He definitely can't bear
to get a divorce from you.

972
00:37:15,840 --> 00:37:17,280
(In Session)

973
00:37:19,280 --> 00:37:21,199
It's over already?

974
00:37:21,200 --> 00:37:22,710
Is it our turn now?

975
00:37:23,070 --> 00:37:24,390
This can't be.

976
00:37:24,550 --> 00:37:26,520
(Court 2, In Session)
It's only been half an hour.

977
00:37:30,360 --> 00:37:32,239
Perhaps this isn't
their first court hearing.

978
00:37:32,240 --> 00:37:33,680
Perhaps they're just
going through the motions.

979
00:37:34,320 --> 00:37:35,520
It'll be fine.

980
00:37:35,640 --> 00:37:37,710
Are you sure the judges
will ask me those questions?

981
00:37:38,160 --> 00:37:39,639
Alright, I'll heed your advice.

982
00:37:39,640 --> 00:37:41,160
I'll file for a divorce
if he doesn't return home.

983
00:37:41,360 --> 00:37:42,429
I'll give him a deadline.

984
00:37:42,430 --> 00:37:43,480
Okay.

985
00:37:45,200 --> 00:37:47,109
Our client has three children.

986
00:37:47,110 --> 00:37:48,879
The defendant insisted

987
00:37:48,880 --> 00:37:50,120
that our client gave birth naturally.

988
00:37:50,200 --> 00:37:52,759
The first child weighs 2.85 kg.

989
00:37:52,760 --> 00:37:55,069
The second child weighs 2.65 kg.

990
00:37:55,070 --> 00:37:57,469
The third child weighs 2.30 kg.

991
00:37:57,470 --> 00:37:59,109
This has caused my client

992
00:37:59,110 --> 00:38:00,680
significant physical harm.

993
00:38:00,990 --> 00:38:02,109
Actually, there's one thing

994
00:38:02,110 --> 00:38:03,759
our client hasn't mentioned.

995
00:38:03,760 --> 00:38:05,600
Perhaps the defendant didn't realize it.

996
00:38:08,030 --> 00:38:10,640
My client actually
didn't want to say this.

997
00:38:10,760 --> 00:38:13,270
This is a major
emotional burden for her.

998
00:38:13,720 --> 00:38:15,319
Her husband never returns home.

999
00:38:15,320 --> 00:38:18,319
My client took care of
the entire family by herself.

1000
00:38:18,320 --> 00:38:19,960
Even when she was tired,
she didn't dare to say so.

1001
00:38:19,990 --> 00:38:22,640
She had no time to rest at all.

1002
00:38:26,110 --> 00:38:27,270
Lihua,

1003
00:38:27,990 --> 00:38:28,949
look at me.

1004
00:38:28,950 --> 00:38:30,750
Defendant, please remain seated.

1005
00:38:32,590 --> 00:38:33,589
I admit.

1006
00:38:33,590 --> 00:38:36,549
You've contributed a lot
to the children's well-being and the family.

1007
00:38:36,550 --> 00:38:38,390
But it's not like I did nothing.

1008
00:38:38,640 --> 00:38:40,029
Ever since you resigned from your job

1009
00:38:40,030 --> 00:38:41,520
and became a full-time housewife,

1010
00:38:41,680 --> 00:38:42,679
the burden of supporting the family

1011
00:38:42,680 --> 00:38:44,429
fell entirely on me.

1012
00:38:44,430 --> 00:38:46,469
I worked my butt off

1013
00:38:46,470 --> 00:38:48,029
all for the sake of the family.

1014
00:38:48,030 --> 00:38:50,040
To think that you're this upset with me.

1015
00:38:50,510 --> 00:38:51,960
I really feel wronged.

1016
00:38:52,840 --> 00:38:53,509
Did he actually say that?

1017
00:38:53,510 --> 00:38:54,069
Tell me.

1018
00:38:54,070 --> 00:38:55,679
Did I go out and pay for a prostitute?

1019
00:38:55,680 --> 00:38:56,879
Or did I go gambling?

1020
00:38:56,880 --> 00:38:58,560
The court can decide.

1021
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:00,430
Judges, take a look.

1022
00:39:00,640 --> 00:39:01,799
Take a look at my schedule

1023
00:39:01,800 --> 00:39:03,080
and work photos.

1024
00:39:12,990 --> 00:39:15,480
This is in the Xi'an High-Tech Zone.

1025
00:39:15,550 --> 00:39:17,430
This is Yinchuan Railway Station.

1026
00:39:17,840 --> 00:39:18,799
There are even farther ones,

1027
00:39:18,800 --> 00:39:20,509
like a secluded mountain valley.

1028
00:39:20,510 --> 00:39:21,799
During my five-day business trip,

1029
00:39:21,800 --> 00:39:23,159
I didn't stop for a moment.

1030
00:39:23,160 --> 00:39:25,069
I went to three provinces
and five cities.

1031
00:39:25,070 --> 00:39:26,759
At the very worst,
I had to work 24 hours straight.

1032
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:28,159
And, I only had an expired protein bar,

1033
00:39:28,160 --> 00:39:29,750
which was the last one I had as well.

1034
00:39:32,110 --> 00:39:33,469
This is Kunshan, Suzhou.

1035
00:39:33,470 --> 00:39:35,870
This is the on-site inspection
in Jiaxing.

1036
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:39,430
That's the wrong one. Next.

1037
00:39:39,520 --> 00:39:41,360
(Panel Judge)

1038
00:39:44,040 --> 00:39:45,989
This is for a trade show in Shanghai.

1039
00:39:45,990 --> 00:39:47,909
The trade show
ran from the 3rd to the 7th.

1040
00:39:47,910 --> 00:39:49,390
I had to be there in advance

1041
00:39:49,680 --> 00:39:51,390
to coordinate with the curators.

1042
00:39:52,160 --> 00:39:53,270
Xianghui.

1043
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:54,870
Swipe up one page.

1044
00:39:56,030 --> 00:39:57,000
Stop.

1045
00:39:58,470 --> 00:39:59,159
Defendant,

1046
00:39:59,160 --> 00:40:00,710
explain the photo.

1047
00:40:01,360 --> 00:40:03,359
This photo was taken

1048
00:40:03,360 --> 00:40:04,279
at a reunion

1049
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:05,750
with my classmates from my MBA.

1050
00:40:05,880 --> 00:40:08,120
I happened to be in Shenzhen
on a business trip at the time.

1051
00:40:08,320 --> 00:40:10,679
My classmates from the area
suggested we grab a meal together.

1052
00:40:10,680 --> 00:40:12,279
It's not related to my work.

1053
00:40:12,280 --> 00:40:13,029
Next photo.

1054
00:40:13,030 --> 00:40:14,830
Who's the girl beside you?

1055
00:40:19,070 --> 00:40:20,230
It's my classmate.

1056
00:40:27,550 --> 00:40:28,750
Jiang Ying?

1057
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:30,350
Is that Jiang Ying?

1058
00:40:30,760 --> 00:40:33,279
I knew you two were having an affair!

1059
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:34,589
Don't slander me.

1060
00:40:34,590 --> 00:40:35,879
The court is a place
where evidence matters.

1061
00:40:35,880 --> 00:40:37,469
You want evidence, huh?

1062
00:40:37,470 --> 00:40:39,359
Fine, I'll give you evidence.

1063
00:40:39,360 --> 00:40:42,120
Sir, she had the same handbag as me!

1064
00:40:42,160 --> 00:40:43,639
You can have your evidence!

1065
00:40:43,640 --> 00:40:45,270
Take a good look!

1066
00:40:46,070 --> 00:40:47,839
Plaintiff, please calm down.

1067
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:48,909
Sir, I'm sorry.

1068
00:40:48,910 --> 00:40:50,679
My client was too agitated just now.

1069
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:52,080
She won't do it again.

1070
00:40:52,360 --> 00:40:54,679
If only you were half
as gentle as Jiang Ying.

1071
00:40:54,680 --> 00:40:56,589
If so, I wouldn't have avoided
returning home, you know?

1072
00:40:56,590 --> 00:40:57,469
Li Zhoucheng.

1073
00:40:57,470 --> 00:41:00,230
Say that again?

1074
00:41:00,640 --> 00:41:03,390
You're heartless.

1075
00:41:03,590 --> 00:41:05,639
You're heartless!

1076
00:41:05,640 --> 00:41:07,159
I've gained so much weight

1077
00:41:07,160 --> 00:41:10,390
just because you wanted children!

1078
00:41:10,950 --> 00:41:12,040
Let's get a divorce.

1079
00:41:12,510 --> 00:41:13,239
Let's get it.

1080
00:41:13,240 --> 00:41:14,389
Sir, I'll get a divorce right now!

1081
00:41:14,390 --> 00:41:15,589
Right now.

1082
00:41:15,590 --> 00:41:16,949
Fine, let's get it, then.

1083
00:41:16,950 --> 00:41:17,909
I agree.

1084
00:41:17,910 --> 00:41:19,640
Both parties, please calm down.

1085
00:41:19,910 --> 00:41:21,799
Do both parties agree to mediation?

1086
00:41:21,800 --> 00:41:22,759
I have to get a divorce.

1087
00:41:22,760 --> 00:41:24,000
I won't agree to mediation either.

1088
00:41:25,160 --> 00:41:26,429
Plaintiff, please confirm

1089
00:41:26,430 --> 00:41:27,429
whether or not a divorce is necessary.

1090
00:41:27,430 --> 00:41:30,549
Look at the situation.
How could I not get a divorce?

1091
00:41:30,550 --> 00:41:31,799
Are you sure about this?

1092
00:41:31,800 --> 00:41:34,000
Our family is shattered entirely.

1093
00:41:34,590 --> 00:41:37,080
There's no way
to piece it together again.

1094
00:41:43,840 --> 00:41:46,120
Given that both sides
are currently highly emotional,

1095
00:41:46,320 --> 00:41:47,839
it's no longer possible
to communicate rationally.

1096
00:41:47,840 --> 00:41:50,200
This is now the third time
this case has been brought to court.

1097
00:41:50,390 --> 00:41:52,870
The courtroom is not a place
to vent one's emotions.

1098
00:41:53,470 --> 00:41:55,639
Don't treat the trial as a joke.

1099
00:41:55,640 --> 00:41:56,839
The court is adjourned.

1100
00:41:56,840 --> 00:41:59,360
(In Session)

1101
00:42:00,840 --> 00:42:01,679
Hey.

1102
00:42:01,680 --> 00:42:04,069
Today really did come as a surprise.

1103
00:42:04,070 --> 00:42:05,239
I've never seen a divorce case

1104
00:42:05,240 --> 00:42:06,549
turn out this unexpectedly.

1105
00:42:07,640 --> 00:42:08,879
Your husband is something else.

1106
00:42:08,880 --> 00:42:10,989
I actually thought he was a workaholic.

1107
00:42:10,990 --> 00:42:12,960
I thought that he was
working outside because...

1108
00:42:14,110 --> 00:42:15,390
Let's forget about it.

1109
00:42:16,280 --> 00:42:18,029
He just wanted you
to babysit his children

1110
00:42:18,030 --> 00:42:19,310
and take care of the family.

1111
00:42:19,320 --> 00:42:20,600
He's disgusting!

1112
00:42:21,360 --> 00:42:23,390
But the judge is pretty impressive.

1113
00:42:23,470 --> 00:42:26,600
I suppose he's practically
leaving Li Zhoucheng penniless now.

1114
00:42:29,950 --> 00:42:31,160
Hey.

1115
00:42:33,240 --> 00:42:34,680
I know.

1116
00:42:34,950 --> 00:42:38,270
This is a huge blow to you.

1117
00:42:38,910 --> 00:42:41,790
Sometimes, life sucks.

1118
00:42:42,680 --> 00:42:43,799
But in my opinion,

1119
00:42:43,800 --> 00:42:45,589
to a strong woman like you,

1120
00:42:45,590 --> 00:42:46,989
this case might not
necessarily be a bad thing.

1121
00:42:46,990 --> 00:42:48,830
And, you're very attractive.

1122
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:50,600
If you...

1123
00:42:50,760 --> 00:42:52,549
If you take care of your appearance,

1124
00:42:52,550 --> 00:42:54,429
and find a trainer at a gym
to get in shape,

1125
00:42:54,430 --> 00:42:55,429
you might just encounter

1126
00:42:55,430 --> 00:42:56,830
the next partner in your life.

1127
00:42:59,510 --> 00:43:01,549
I don't want another partner!

1128
00:43:01,550 --> 00:43:03,560
I only want my husband!

1129
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

1130
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

1131
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

1132
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1133
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1134
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1135
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

1136
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

1137
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

1138
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

1139
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

1140
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1141
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1142
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1143
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

1144
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

1145
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

1146
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

1147
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

1148
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

1149
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

1150
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

1151
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:37,310
♪All the little things♪

1152
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:40,010
♪Woven into our lives♪

1153
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:42,880
♪The building blocks of life♪

1154
00:44:42,880 --> 00:44:44,590
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1155
00:44:44,590 --> 00:44:47,040
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1156
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:49,150
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1157
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:51,530
♪Some questions♪

1158
00:44:52,100 --> 00:44:54,800
♪Weigh like mountains♪

1159
00:44:57,690 --> 00:45:02,840
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1160
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:07,130
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1161
00:45:07,310 --> 00:45:12,360
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1162
00:45:12,730 --> 00:45:16,430
♪Where fairness stands♪

1163
00:45:16,600 --> 00:45:19,680
♪Within the law♪

1164
00:45:20,840 --> 00:45:29,520
♪And within every heart♪
